svg.text: The Rings and Satellites of Saturn
Saturn's largest moon Titan discovered by Christiaan Huygens
Christiaan Huygens makes first observations of Saturn's rings
Pioneer 11 is the first spacecraft to visit Saturn
Voyager 1 reaches Saturn, taking the first high-resolution images of the planet
Voyager 2 arrives at Saturn, en route to the outer Solar System
CassiniHuygens spacecraft arrives at Saturn, remains in the system until 2017
Huygens probe parachutes through the atmosphere of Titan, lands on its surface
Geysers of liquid water seen erupting from the surface of Enceladus
Cassini missions ends, orbiter descends into Saturn's atmosphere
